Name: Types of differential object marking
Description:
Symmetric Type I: DOM in pronouns, personal names, and common nouns by means of two or more different overt (case) markers
Symmetric Type II: DOM in pronouns and personal nouns only by means of two or more different overt (case) markers
Symmetric Type III: DOM in pronouns only by means of two or more different overt (case) markers
Asymmetric Type I: DOM in pronouns, personal names, and common nouns distinguishing unmarked base forms from more specific, marked forms
Asymmetric Type II: DOM in pronouns and personal nouns only distinguishing unmarked base forms from more specific, marked forms
Asymmetric Type III: DOM in pronouns only distinguishing unmarked base forms from more specific, marked forms
